###### Definition 3.1 (Triangular kernel on \mathbb{Z}/N\mathbb{Z}).

Let N\geq 2 and let r be an integer with 1\leq r\leq\lfloor N/2\rfloor. For n\in\mathbb{Z}/N\mathbb{Z} let |n| denote the least absolute value representative in \{-\lfloor N/2\rfloor,\dots,\lfloor N/2\rfloor\}. Define F\_{r}:\mathbb{Z}/N\mathbb{Z}\to[0,\infty) by

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
|  | F\_{r}(n):=\frac{1}{r}\,\max\Bigl{(}0,\,1-\frac{|n|}{r}\Bigr{)},\qquad n\in% \mathbb{Z}/N\mathbb{Z}. |  | (1) |

Equivalently, F\_{r} is supported on \{|n|\leq r-1\} and has the triangular shape

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
|  | F\_{r}(n)=\frac{1}{r}\Bigl{(}1-\frac{|n|}{r}\Bigr{)}\quad\text{for }|n|\leq r-1% ,\qquad F\_{r}(n)=0\ \text{otherwise}. |  |

Since r\leq N/2, this definition is unambiguous on \mathbb{Z}/N\mathbb{Z} (the support does not wrap around the circle). A direct computation shows that F\_{r} is nonnegative, even, and has unit mass.

###### Lemma 3.2 (Basic properties of F\_{r}).

Let N\geq 2 and 1\leq r\leq\lfloor N/2\rfloor. Then F\_{r}:\mathbb{Z}/N\mathbb{Z}\to\mathbb{R}\_{\geq 0} satisfies:

1. 1.

   (Support) F\_{r}(n)=0 for |n|\geq r.
2. 2.

   (Symmetry) F\_{r}(-n)=F\_{r}(n) for all n\in\mathbb{Z}/N\mathbb{Z}.
3. 3.

   (Unit mass) \displaystyle\sum\_{n\in\mathbb{Z}/N\mathbb{Z}}F\_{r}(n)=1.

